<%- include('partials/header.ejs') %>
<div class="container py-5" style="min-height: 100vh; background-color: #f8f9fa;">
  <div class="text-center mb-4">
    <h1 class="display-5" style="font-weight: bold; color: #0035ff;">Help & Tutorial</h1>
    <p class="text-muted">Learn how to use the features of our website effectively.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="row" style = "padding-top:50px;">
    <div class="col-lg-8 offset-lg-2">
      <h2>Website Features</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>View FIRs:</strong> Browse all registered FIRs or search by FIR number.</li>
        <li><strong>FIR Details:</strong> View comprehensive details of an FIR, including sections applied and suspects.</li>
        <li><strong>Generate FIR:</strong> Create a new FIR by filling out a form with necessary details like complainant information, location, and suspects.</li>
        <li><strong>BNS Sections:</strong> Explore the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita chapters and their sections in detail.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How to Use</h2>
      <h5>1. View Past Complains</h5>
      <p>Navigate to the "View FIRs" section to see all FIRs or use the search bar to find a specific FIR by number.</p>

      <h5>2. File an FIR</h5>
      <p>Go to the "Generate FIR" section and fill out the required details. Include the complainant's name, phone number, address, and details of the incident. Submit the form to register the FIR.</p>

      <h5>3. Exploring BNS Sections</h5>
      <p>Visit the "BNS Sections" section to learn about different chapters and sections under the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita.</p>

      <h5>4. Viewing FIR Details</h5>
      <p>Click on any FIR to see its details, including the incident location, time, applied sections, and suspects.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
